==========================================================
STEP 6 - LAYER 0 ANALYSIS (INGESTION)
==========================================================

Studied the first layer of the architecture.

Purpose:

Receive uploaded PDF files before any processing.

Responsibilities:

- Validate uploaded file
- Verify PDF extension
- Reject invalid files
- Generate unique Job ID
- Store original PDF
- Return Job ID to client

Pipeline:

Client
   │
Upload PDF
   │
Validation
   │
Job creation
   │
Store original PDF
   │
Return Job ID

==========================================================
JOB CONCEPT
==========================================================

A Job represents one document processing request.

Each uploaded PDF receives a unique identifier (UUID).

Example:

Job
---------------------------
job_id
filename
status
created_at

Future status values:

RECEIVED
ANALYZING
CLASSIFYING
EXTRACTING
VALIDATING
MATCHING
COMPLETED
FAILED

==========================================================
PDF STORAGE
==========================================================

Initial idea:

Local storage:

backend/storage/uploads/

Final architecture:

FastAPI
    │
Validation
    │
MinIO Object Storage
    │
Original PDF stored
    │
PostgreSQL stores metadata only

==========================================================
MINIO
==========================================================

Decision:

Use MinIO instead of local storage.

Reason:

- S3 compatible
- Production-like architecture
- Better separation between files and database
- Easy migration to AWS S3 later

Current status:

Downloading and configuring MinIO.

Pending:

- Install minio.exe
- Create C:\minio
- Create bucket "documents"
- Connect FastAPI to MinIO

